long_desc.thetext:
If I set a tooltip for a header column in a table, I can't remove the tolltip without setting a new header cell renderer.

Example:

headerCellRenderer.setToolTip("Some text");

Now a tooltip containing the text "Some text" is shown if I hover the header cell.

headerCellRenderer.resetToolTip();

The tooltip still contains "Some text".

headerCellRenderer.setToolTip("");

The tooltip is shown with an empty text.


The bug seems to be here: https://github.com/qooxdoo/qooxdoo/blob/master/framework/source/class/qx/ui/table/headerrenderer/Default.js#L112


If I call resetToolTip() or setToolTip(null) the tooltip should be removed from the header cell. At least, that is my expected behavior.
